<subSubSection id="C32512ABAB04FFD1FF6CFA56FBE2FA3D" pageId="8" pageNumber="125" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B804120AB04FFD1FF6CFA56FBE2FA3D" blockId="8.[151,1437,1270,2015]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis id="B94B9D32AB04FFD1FF6CFA56FED1FA61" bold="true" box="[199,334,1414,1439]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Etymology.</emphasis>
The epithet, to be treated as a noun in apposition, is a word used in 
<collectingCountry id="F32801B0AB04FFD1FBE1FA56FB11FA61" box="[1098,1166,1414,1439]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Brazil</collectingCountry>
for black water flooded forest in the Amazon, since the specimens reported here were collected from that habitat.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32512ABAB04FFD1FF6CFA1EFEC7F989" pageId="8" pageNumber="125" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B804120AB04FFD1FF6CFA1EFEC7F989" blockId="8.[151,1437,1270,2015]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis id="B94B9D32AB04FFD1FF6CFA1EFEDEFA19" bold="true" box="[199,321,1486,1511]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of this species can be recognized by having the embolus with no abrupt angle (
<figureCitation id="13045DA5AB04FFD1FB54FA1EFACFFA19" box="[1279,1360,1486,1511]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F3AA3AB04FFD1FA2FFA1FFF7DF9F4" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Edwardsya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simoni">
<emphasis id="B94B9D32AB04FFD1FA2FFA1FFF7DF9F4" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">E. simoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the embolus extends straight distally and then forms an angle at its middle; see 
<figureCitation id="13045DA5AB04FFD1FBDAFA22FB5DF9F5" box="[1137,1218,1522,1547]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1619,1642]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,208,1590]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1598]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 16. Edwardsya simoni comb. nov. 10 – 14 left male palp (10 proventral; 11 vetral; 12 retroventral; 13 retrolateral; 14 dorsal); 15 epigyne, ventral; 16 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; PTA = prolateral tibial apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263810/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Also, males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F3AA3AB04FFD1FA2FFA23FF48F9D0" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Edwardsya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="igapo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94B9D32AB04FFD1FA2FFA23FF48F9D0" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">E. igapo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2782049AB04FFD1FF75F9C6FEA7F9D1" box="[222,312,1558,1583]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B94B9D32AB04FFD1FF75F9C6FEA7F9D1" bold="true" box="[222,312,1558,1583]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
have larger terminal apophysis and smaller RTA (
<figureCitation id="13045DA5AB04FFD1FCC7F9C6FC5FF9D1" box="[876,960,1558,1583]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
). Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F3AA3AB04FFD1FBFCF9C7FB29F9D0" box="[1111,1206,1559,1582]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Edwardsya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="igapo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94B9D32AB04FFD1FBFCF9C7FB29F9D0" box="[1111,1206,1559,1582]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">E. igapo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2782049AB04FFD1FB16F9C6FA88F9D1" box="[1213,1303,1558,1583]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B94B9D32AB04FFD1FB16F9C6FA88F9D1" bold="true" box="[1213,1303,1558,1583]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
have round copulatory openings, the spermathecae are larger and the dorsal coupling pocket is not centralized, almost paired (
<figureCitation id="13045DA5AB04FFD1FF34F98EFF6AF989" box="[159,245,1630,1655]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1554,1577]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,221,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,221,1513]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 39 male, dorsal; 40 – 41 left male palp (40 ventral; 41 retrolateral); 42 female, dorsal; 43 epigyne, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164528/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Figs 43</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13045DA5AB04FFD1FEAAF98FFED3F989" box="[257,332,1631,1655]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">48–49</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32512ABAB04FFD0FF6CF952FB08FEBE" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="126" pageId="8" pageNumber="125" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B804120AB04FFD1FF6CF952FECBF869" blockId="8.[151,1437,1270,2015]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis id="B94B9D32AB04FFD1FF6CF952FDB3F965" bold="true" box="[199,556,1666,1691]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">
Description. Male (
<typeStatus id="5484FF82AB04FFD1FE19F952FD80F965" box="[434,543,1666,1691]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">holotype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length: 5.91. Although the specimen is not perfectly preserved, color pattern as described for the genus (
<figureCitation id="13045DA5AB04FFD1FDB1F976FDF1F941" box="[538,622,1702,1727]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1554,1577]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,221,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,221,1513]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 39 male, dorsal; 40 – 41 left male palp (40 ventral; 41 retrolateral); 42 female, dorsal; 43 epigyne, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164528/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
). Carapace 3.07 long, 2.23 wide, 1.69 high. Ocular quadrangle 1.77 long. Anterior eye row 2.23 wide and posterior 2.00 wide. Palp as described for the genus (
<figureCitation id="13045DA5AB04FFD1FBD5F91AFA9DF91D" box="[1150,1282,1738,1763]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1554,1577]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,221,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,221,1513]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 39 male, dorsal; 40 – 41 left male palp (40 ventral; 41 retrolateral); 42 female, dorsal; 43 epigyne, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164528/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Figs 40–41</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13045DA5AB04FFD1FABAF91BFAC4F91D" box="[1297,1371,1739,1763]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">44–47</figureCitation>
). Leg formula: 3412. Length of femur: I 1.78, II 1.70, III 2.18, IV 1.92; patella + tibia: I 2.30, II 2.06, III 2.16, IV 2.02; metatarsus + tarsus: I 1.58, II 1.61, III 2.09, IV 2.23. Leg macrosetae: femur I d1-1-1, p2di, r0; II d1-1-1, p2di, r0- 1-2; III d1-1-1, p0-1-2, r1di; IV d1-1-1, p1di, r1di; patella I=II p1, r0; III=IV p1, r1; tibia I p1-1-1, r0, 
<date id="FF8167E0AB04FFD1FA8DF8E7FAC7F8B1" box="[1318,1368,1847,1871]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">v2-1</date>
r-2; II p1-2-1, r0, 
<date id="FF8167E0AB04FFD1FEB3F88BFED6F88D" box="[280,329,1883,1907]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">v2-1</date>
r-2; III=IV p1-1-1, r2-1-1, 
<date id="FF8167E0AB04FFD1FDD6F88BFD08F88D" box="[637,663,1883,1907]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">v1</date>
p-0-2; metatarsus I=II 
<date id="FF8167E0AB04FFD1FC30F88BFC4EF88D" box="[923,977,1883,1907]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">v2-2</date>
; III p1-0-2, r1-1-2, 
<date id="FF8167E0AB04FFD1FB18F88BFB52F88D" box="[1203,1229,1883,1907]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">v1</date>
p-1r-2; IV p1-1-2, r2-1-2, 
<date id="FF8167E0AB04FFD1FF40F8AFFE9AF869" box="[235,261,1919,1943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">v1</date>
p-1r-2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B804120AB04FFD0FF6CF872FB08FEBE" blockId="8.[151,1437,1270,2015]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1437,151,464]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="126" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis id="B94B9D32AB04FFD1FF6CF872FE30F845" bold="true" box="[199,431,1954,1979]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">
Female (
<typeStatus id="5484FF82AB04FFD1FE9AF872FE3CF845" box="[305,419,1954,1979]" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">paratype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length: 6.22. Although the specimen is not perfectly preserved, color pattern as described for the genus (
<figureCitation id="13045DA5AB04FFD1FE00F816FE60F821" box="[427,511,1990,2015]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1554,1577]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,221,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,221,1513]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 39 male, dorsal; 40 – 41 left male palp (40 ventral; 41 retrolateral); 42 female, dorsal; 43 epigyne, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164528/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="125">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
). Carapace 3.07 long, 2.07 wide, 1.46 high. Ocular quadrangle 1.54 long. Anterior eye row 2.00 wide and posterior 1.84 wide. Leg formula: 3412. Length of femur: I 1.51, II 1.51, III 2.02, IV 1.78; patella + tibia: I 2.06, II 1.87, III 2.09, IV 1.94; metatarsus + tarsus: I 1.39, II 1.34, III 1.90, IV 2.02. Leg macrosetae: femur I d1-1-1, p1di, r0; II=III d1-1-1, p2di, r0; IV d1-1-1, p0, r1di; patella I=II 0; III=IV p1, r1; tibia I p0-1-1, r0, 
<date id="FF8167E0AB05FFD0FE8FFED4FEC9FEE2" box="[292,342,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="126">v2-1</date>
r-2; II p1-1-1, r0, 
<date id="FF8167E0AB05FFD0FDB7FED4FDD1FEE2" box="[540,590,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="126">v2-1</date>
r-2; III=IV p1-1-1, r1-1-1, 
<date id="FF8167E0AB05FFD0FCD1FED4FC0BFEE2" box="[890,916,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="126">v1</date>
p-0-2; metatarsus I=II 
<date id="FF8167E0AB05FFD0FB39FED4FB57FEE2" box="[1170,1224,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="126">v2-2</date>
; III p1-0-2, r1-1-2, 
<date id="FF8167E0AB05FFD0FF3CFEF8FF2EFEBE" box="[151,177,296,320]" pageId="9" pageNumber="126">v1</date>
p-1r-2; IV p1-1-2, r2-1-2, 
<date id="FF8167E0AB05FFD0FE73FEF8FE6DFEBE" box="[472,498,296,320]" pageId="9" pageNumber="126">v1</date>
p-1r-2. Epigyne as described for the genus (
<figureCitation id="13045DA5AB05FFD0FC76FEF7FBABFEBE" box="[989,1076,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1554,1577]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,221,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,221,1513]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 39 male, dorsal; 40 – 41 left male palp (40 ventral; 41 retrolateral); 42 female, dorsal; 43 epigyne, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164528/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="126">Figs 43</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13045DA5AB05FFD0FBEBFEF8FB14FEBE" box="[1088,1163,296,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 49" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1547,1570]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,208,1513]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 49. Edwardsya igapo sp. nov. 44 – 47 left male palp (44 ventral; 45 disto-proventral; 46 retrolateral; 47 retroventral); 48 epigyne, ventral; 49 same, cleared, dorsal; dCP = dorsal coupling pocket; E = embolus; FDA = femoral distal apophysis; TmA = terminal apophysis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263816/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="126">48–49</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32512ABAB05FFD0FF6CFE9CFB40FE53" pageId="9" pageNumber="126" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B804120AB05FFD0FF6CFE9CFB40FE53" blockId="9.[151,1437,151,464]" pageId="9" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis id="B94B9D32AB05FFD0FF6CFE9CFEB8FE9B" bold="true" box="[199,295,332,357]" pageId="9" pageNumber="126">Biology.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAE3CD1AB05FFD0FE67FE9CFDECFE9A" author="Adis" box="[460,627,332,357]" pageId="9" pageNumber="126" refString="Adis, J. (2002) Sampling sites at Manaus. In: Adis, J. Amazonian Arachnida and Myriapoda. Pensoft, Bulgaria, 590 pp." type="book" year="2002">Adis (2002: 8)</bibRefCitation>
, the 
<typeStatus id="5484FF82AB05FFD0FD07FE9DFD43FE9B" box="[684,732,333,357]" pageId="9" pageNumber="126">type</typeStatus>
locality is covered with a clayish-sandy soil, being inundated for about four months every year, which agrees with the description of the locality in Belém where 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F3AA3AB05FFD0FABFFEA1FA1FFE79" box="[1300,1408,368,392]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Edwardsya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simoni">
<emphasis id="B94B9D32AB05FFD0FABFFEA1FA1FFE79" box="[1300,1408,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="126">E. simoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found. This seasonal 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F3AA3AB05FFD0FE2EFE44FDDFFE52" authority="in Manaus" authorityName="in Manaus" box="[389,576,404,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Edwardsya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="igapo">igapó in Manaus</taxonomicName>
has been periodically flooded for at least one million years.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32512ABAB05FFD0FF6CFE67FD57FE2E" box="[199,712,439,464]" pageId="9" pageNumber="126" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B804120AB05FFD0FF6CFE67FD57FE2E" blockId="9.[151,1437,151,464]" box="[199,712,439,464]" pageId="9" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis id="B94B9D32AB05FFD0FF6CFE67FEFFFE2E" bold="true" box="[199,352,439,464]" pageId="9" pageNumber="126">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from 
<typeStatus id="5484FF82AB05FFD0FD9CFE68FDF8FE2E" box="[567,615,440,464]" pageId="9" pageNumber="126">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
